
[1]sacredly

   SA'CREDLY, adv.

   1. Religiously; with due reverence as of something holy or consecrated
   to God; as, to observe the sabbath sacredly; the day is sacredly kept.

   2. Inviolably; strictly; as, to observe one's word sacredly; a secret
   to be sacredly kept.
